{%- comment -%}
  Shoppable Videos (Card Layouts) — JS-rendered card strip + dialog player.

  Wrapper contract (per docs/tech/studio-liquid-snippets.md "Library Snippets"):
    - variant            : default variant from mo.variants.value.variants
    - slot               : matched shoppable_videos slot entry
    - slot_payload       : slot.payload.value
    - entry              : resolved content entry from the slot payload
    - videos_union       : union of videos referenced by every slotKey used by variants
    - mo                 : spectrum_snippet_instance metaobject drop
    - mutation_handle    : 'mut-{instanceId}' (consumed by wrapper outer div)
    - experience_handle  : (consumed by wrapper outer div)

  variant.content fields:
    - heading      string (optional)                                   section heading
    - subheading   string (optional)                                   supporting copy under heading
    - card_style   'plain' | 'stacked' | 'overlay'                     listing card layout;
                                                                       applied as BEM modifier on the host
                                                                       (no modifier emitted for 'plain').
                                                                       The lightbox is identical across all
                                                                       three; only the listing card differs.
    - cta_text     string (optional, default 'Shop now')               label on the lightbox product-card CTA.
    - cta_action   'redirect' | 'mini_pdp' (default 'redirect')        what the CTA does. 'redirect' is an
                                                                       anchor to the product URL. 'mini_pdp'
                                                                       opens an in-lightbox bottom sheet with
                                                                       a variant picker. Single-variant +
                                                                       available products always perform a
                                                                       direct add-to-cart and skip the sheet
                                                                       regardless of this setting.
  entry.content fields:
    - videoHandles string[]                                            references resolved
                                                                       client-side against the bespoke pool

  Render strategy:
  - SSR emits the shell, heading/subheading, ONE skeleton placeholder per refId,
    the dialog scaffold (close/mute/nav buttons + empty __dialog-slides), and
    the bespoke pool block. No matching against the instance metaobject at
    SSR time; no per-video URL/poster resolution at the cards/slides sites.
  - The asset JS (loaded async) reads the pool, calls applyVariant on init AND
    on every targeting swap, and rebuilds the strip in the chosen card_style:
    each refId either becomes a real <button class="__card"> (pool entry has
    video_url) or a styled <div class="__card __card--unavailable"> indicator
    (pool entry missing or no video_url — visible-degraded mode per project
    error-handling philosophy). Stacked and overlay card styles also embed the
    first product_tag's thumb + title + price inside the same single tap target.
  - Skeleton placeholders share the __card class so CSS aspect-ratio + width
    apply unchanged → no CLS when JS swaps placeholder → real card.
  - Only real cards open the dialog; unavailable indicators are aria-hidden
    and pointer-events:none. The whole listing card is one tap target — taps
    on the embedded product info also open the dialog.

  Pool block (rich JSON) is the single source of truth for per-video data:
  resolved video URL (mp4 picked server-side), poster URL (image_url filter
  applied), and the full product_tags array with money filters and
  image_url filters applied. JS string-builders consume it directly.

  Forked from packages/snippet-library/snippets/svmk8tqx/ — that snippet stays
  in the catalog and is independently maintained. Bug fixes to lightbox / dialog
  behaviour do not auto-flow between the two; coordinate when touching either.

  NOTE: do not write literal comment or doc tag syntax in documentation
  text — Shopify Liquid nests those tags and will reject the file on
  theme write.
{%- endcomment -%}

{% stylesheet %}
/* Shoppable Videos (Card Layouts) (jzqlk4g5) */

/* Shoppable Videos — aggregated into spectrum-snippet.css at install */

/* ───── 1. Block-root tokens ───── */

.sai-jzqlk4g5 {
  --sai-jzqlk4g5-gap: var(--sai-size-3);
}

/* ───── 2. Section shell ───── */

.sai-jzqlk4g5__container {
  max-width: var(--sai-page-width);
  margin-inline: auto;
  padding-block: var(--sai-size-6);
  padding-inline: var(--sai-size-4);
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-block-end: var(--sai-size-4);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__heading {
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  margin: 0;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__subheading {
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-body-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight);
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.65;
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  margin: 0.75rem auto 0;
  max-width: 42rem;
}

/* ───── 3. Card strip — mobile-first base (horizontal scroll-snap) ───── */

.sai-jzqlk4g5__grid {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  gap: var(--sai-jzqlk4g5-gap);
  overflow-x: auto;
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  scrollbar-width: none;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
  width: fit-content;
  max-width: 100%;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__grid::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card {
  position: relative;
  aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  cursor: pointer;
  background: transparent;
  border: none;
  padding: 0;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  width: 38vw;
  min-width: 130px;
  scroll-snap-align: start;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-video {
  aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
  display: block;
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  transition: transform var(--sai-duration-3) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-video > img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-poster {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
  transition: transform var(--sai-duration-3) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:hover .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-video,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:focus-visible .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-video,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:hover .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-poster,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:focus-visible .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-poster {
  transform: scale(1.04);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__play {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  transition: background var(--sai-duration-2) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:hover .sai-jzqlk4g5__play,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:focus-visible .sai-jzqlk4g5__play {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__play-btn {
  width: 52px;
  height: 52px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88);
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
  transition: transform var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1), background
    var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:hover .sai-jzqlk4g5__play-btn,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card:focus-visible .sai-jzqlk4g5__play-btn {
  transform: scale(1.1);
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1);
}

/* Placeholder + unavailable share the same slot dimensions as a real card
   (aspect-ratio + width inherited from .sai-jzqlk4g5__card above) so the
   JS swap from placeholder → real-or-unavailable is CLS-free. Both are
   inert (pointer-events:none, aria-hidden) — only real cards open the
   dialog. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card--placeholder,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card--unavailable {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  cursor: default;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card--unavailable {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  color: var(--sai-color-fg);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 8px;
  opacity: 0.6;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card--unavailable::after {
  content: "Video unavailable";
}

/* ───── 4. Dialog — mobile-first base (vertical scroll-snap) ───── */

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog {
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 0;
  width: 100vw;
  max-width: 100vw;
  height: 100dvh;
  max-height: 100dvh;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: #000;
  margin: 0;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog[open] {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  animation: sai-jzqlk4g5-dialog-fadein var(--sai-duration-2) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

@keyframes sai-jzqlk4g5-dialog-fadein {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
  }
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog::backdrop {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-close {
  position: absolute;
  top: 16px;
  left: 12px;
  z-index: 20;
  width: 36px;
  height: 36px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  border: none;
  border-radius: 50%;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 0;
  transition: background var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-close:hover {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-close:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #fff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-mute {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 140px;
  right: 12px;
  z-index: 20;
  width: 36px;
  height: 36px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  border: none;
  border-radius: 50%;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 0;
  transition: background var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-mute:hover {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-mute:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #fff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav {
  display: none;
}

/* Class rule above (and the tablet+ override at min-width:768px) wins
   against the UA `[hidden]` rule by specificity, so without this explicit
   override the JS-toggled `hidden` attribute would silently fail to hide
   nav buttons on tablet+. Same idiom used for __product-btn[hidden]. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slides {
  display: block;
  overflow-x: hidden;
  overflow-y: scroll;
  scroll-snap-type: y mandatory;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  overscroll-behavior: contain;
  scrollbar-width: none;
  height: 100dvh;
  position: relative;
  flex: 1;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slides::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  min-height: 100dvh;
  height: 100dvh;
  max-height: 100dvh;
  scroll-snap-align: start;
  background: #000;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-video {
  aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
  display: block;
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  width: 100%;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-video > img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
}

/* ───── 5. Lightbox product card strip — multi-product, scroll-snap ─────
   One card per tagged product, snap-aligned in a horizontal strip. The
   strip is anchored to the bottom of the 9:16 dialog frame with a gradient
   mask for legibility. One card visible at a time with the next peeking on
   the right; mobile swipe / desktop scroll. Each card is its own tap target
   with its own CTA (redirect / direct-ATC / mini-PDP / OOS). */

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-products {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  z-index: 10;
  padding: 12px 12px 16px;
  background: linear-gradient(
    to top,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.72) 0%,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4) 60%,
    transparent 100%
  );
  pointer-events: auto;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-products-scroll {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  gap: 10px;
  overflow-x: auto;
  overflow-y: hidden;
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  scrollbar-width: none;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-products-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__product-card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr auto;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 8px 10px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
  color: #1a1a1a;
  border-radius: 12px;
  text-decoration: none;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  width: 92%;
  max-width: 360px;
  scroll-snap-align: start;
}

/* Single-product slide: when there's only one product card in the strip,
   the "next card peeks out" affordance has nothing to peek to. Bump to
   100% width with no max-width cap so the lone card uses the full dialog
   width and looks intentional rather than ~80% with empty space beside it. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-products-scroll > .sai-jzqlk4g5__product-card:only-child {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__product-image-wrap {
  display: block;
  width: 60px;
  height: 60px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  border-radius: 8px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__product-meta {
  min-width: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2px;
  text-align: left;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__product-title {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.3;
  color: #1a1a1a;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__product-price {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1.2;
  color: #1a1a1a;
  opacity: 0.8;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__cta {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 8px 14px;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: #121212;
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 6px;
  cursor: pointer;
  text-decoration: none;
  white-space: nowrap;
  line-height: 1;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__cta:hover:not(:disabled) {
  opacity: 0.9;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__cta:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #fff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__cta:disabled {
  opacity: 0.4;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

/* ───── 5b. Mini-PDP bottom sheet (quickshop) ─────
   Activated when cta_action='mini_pdp' and the tagged product has multiple
   variants. Single-variant products skip the sheet (direct ATC). The sheet
   is a sibling of __dialog-slides so swipe / scroll on slides doesn't
   transform it. Theme color + font variables only. */

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 12;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-end;
  justify-content: center;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-backdrop {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
  transition: background 0.25s ease;
  pointer-events: auto;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop--open .sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-backdrop {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-panel {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  width: 100%;
  max-height: 88%;
  background: rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  border-radius: 16px 16px 0 0;
  padding: 20px 20px 22px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  transform: translateY(100%);
  transition: transform 0.28s cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1);
  pointer-events: auto;
  overflow-y: auto;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 18px;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop--open .sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-panel {
  transform: translateY(0);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-close {
  position: absolute;
  top: 12px;
  right: 12px;
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  padding: 0;
  background: transparent;
  border: none;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  cursor: pointer;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-close:hover {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-close:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-header {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 130px 1fr;
  gap: 16px;
  align-items: flex-start;
  padding-right: 36px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-media {
  width: 130px;
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
  border-radius: 8px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-image {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-meta {
  min-width: 0;
  padding-top: 4px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-title {
  display: block;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading, var(--sai-font-body));
  font-size: 17px;
  line-height: 1.25;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  text-decoration: none;
  margin: 0 0 8px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-title:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-price {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 6px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-price-compare {
  font-weight: 400;
  text-decoration: line-through;
  opacity: 0.55;
  font-size: 13px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-view {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
  margin-top: 6px;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  opacity: 0.55;
  text-decoration: none;
  transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-view:hover,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-view:focus-visible {
  opacity: 0.85;
  text-decoration: underline;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-view-icon {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  display: inline-block;
}

/* Options list — N stacked group cards. Each attribute (Size, Color…) gets
   a card-shaped container with its own pill row, keeping multi-attribute
   products legible at a glance. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-options {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 12px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-group {
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 12px 14px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-group-head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 6px;
  font-size: 13px;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-group-name {
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  opacity: 0.55;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-group-selected {
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  font-weight: 600;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-group-pills {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 8px;
}

/* Pills — three flavors. Text-only is default; swatch-color and swatch-image
   add a leading visual marker. OOS pills line through and dim. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill {
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  min-width: 64px;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  background: rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
  line-height: 1.2;
  text-align: center;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill:hover {
  border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill--selected,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill--selected:hover {
  border-color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  border-width: 2px;
  /* Compensate for the +1px border so the pill doesn't shift on select. */
  padding: 9px 13px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill--oos {
  opacity: 0.45;
  text-decoration: line-through;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill-swatch {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 18px;
  height: 18px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill--swatch-color .sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill-swatch,
.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill--swatch-image .sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill-swatch {
  /* Crisp ring at swatch level mirrors the pill's selected ring. */
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-pill-label {
  display: inline-block;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-atc {
  width: 100%;
  margin-top: 4px;
  padding: 18px 20px;
  background: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  color: rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading, var(--sai-font-body));
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-atc:hover:not(:disabled) {
  opacity: 0.88;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-atc:disabled {
  opacity: 0.4;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-atc:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* ───── 6. Tablet+ (@media min-width: 768px) — horizontal card sizing + desktop dialog ───── */

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .sai-jzqlk4g5__card {
    width: 25vw;
    min-width: 180px;
    max-width: 260px;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-close {
    top: 16px;
    right: 16px;
    left: auto;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-mute {
    top: 64px;
    right: 16px;
    bottom: auto;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav {
    display: flex;
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    z-index: 20;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50%;
    cursor: pointer;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 0;
    transition: background var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #fff;
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: default;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav--prev {
    left: 24px;
  }
  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav--next {
    right: 24px;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slides {
    display: flex;
    position: relative;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    overflow: hidden;
    overflow-y: hidden;
    scroll-snap-type: none;
    min-height: 0;
    height: auto;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide {
    position: absolute;
    width: min(380px, calc(100vw - 180px));
    aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
    max-height: 82dvh;
    min-height: 0;
    height: auto;
    max-width: none;
    border-radius: 14px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #000;
    transition: transform 0.4s var(--sai-ease-out-1), opacity 0.4s var(--sai-ease-out-1);
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slides--snap .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide {
    transition: none;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide[data-position="center"] {
    transform: translateX(0) scale(1);
    opacity: 1;
    z-index: 3;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide[data-position="left"] {
    transform: translateX(calc(-100% - 48px)) scale(0.85);
    opacity: 0.35;
    z-index: 2;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide[data-position="right"] {
    transform: translateX(calc(100% + 48px)) scale(0.85);
    opacity: 0.35;
    z-index: 2;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide[data-position="hidden"] {
    transform: translateX(200%) scale(0.7);
    opacity: 0;
    z-index: 1;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-products {
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide[data-position="center"] .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-products {
    pointer-events: auto;
  }
}

/* ───── 7. Card-style modifiers (stacked / overlay) ─────
   The strip stays horizontally scrollable for all three card styles. Plain
   mode emits no modifier and uses the original markup directly under .__card
   (no .__card-media wrapper). Stacked and overlay wrap the media + play icon
   in .__card-media and append .__card-product as a sibling — sized differently
   per modifier. The product info is informational-only (aria-hidden inside
   the parent <button>); the lightbox is the full a11y surface. */

/* Inner media wrapper — only present when card_style is stacked or overlay.
   Inherits the 9/16 video aspect-ratio so .__card-poster / .__card-video
   continue to render unchanged. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-media {
  position: relative;
  aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
  width: 100%;
  overflow: hidden;
  border-radius: inherit;
}

/* Listing-surface product card — base shared by stacked + overlay.
   Background is hardcoded to white because the per-theme `--sai-color-bg`
   token sometimes resolves to a transparent / non-paint value in merchant
   themes — the fallback in `var(... , #fff)` wouldn't kick in then. White
   is the intended brand visual for the listing product card; merchants who
   need a different colour can override per-instance via the `card_product`
   style node (meta.json). */
.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product {
  background: #fff;
  color: var(--sai-color-fg, #111);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-size: var(--sai-text-size-2, 13px);
  line-height: var(--sai-text-leading-2, 1.3);
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-info {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2, 8px);
  padding: var(--sai-size-2, 8px);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-img {
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  border-radius: 6px;
  object-fit: cover;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-text {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2px;
  min-width: 0;
  flex: 1;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-title {
  font-weight: 500;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-price {
  font-weight: 600;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

/* ── Stacked: video on top, product info as a sibling below with a small gap.
   Drops the outer card's aspect-ratio so the tile grows naturally — height
   = media height + product band. The strip is still horizontally scrollable;
   tiles are just taller in this mode. ── */
.sai-jzqlk4g5--stacked .sai-jzqlk4g5__card {
  aspect-ratio: auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  background: var(--sai-color-bg, #fff);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5--stacked .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product {
  margin-top: var(--sai-size-2, 8px);
  border-radius: 8px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5--stacked .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-info {
  padding: var(--sai-size-2, 8px) var(--sai-size-3, 12px);
}

/* Reserve room below stacked placeholders so the JS swap-in doesn't push the
   surrounding page content down. Soft reservation; exact product-band height
   is token-driven so this is approximate. */
.sai-jzqlk4g5--stacked .sai-jzqlk4g5__card--placeholder {
  aspect-ratio: auto;
  height: 0;
  padding-bottom: calc(56vw + 64px);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .sai-jzqlk4g5--stacked .sai-jzqlk4g5__card--placeholder {
    padding-bottom: calc((38vw * 16 / 9) + 64px);
  }
}

/* ── Overlay: white-bg pill near the bottom of the video. Inset on left,
   right, and bottom; a soft drop shadow lifts it off the video. ── */
.sai-jzqlk4g5--overlay .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product--overlay {
  position: absolute;
  left: 8px;
  right: 8px;
  bottom: 8px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
  backdrop-filter: blur(2px);
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5--overlay .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product--overlay .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-info {
  padding: 6px 8px;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5--overlay .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product--overlay .sai-jzqlk4g5__card-product-img {
  width: 36px;
  height: 36px;
}

/* ───── 8. Story progress bar + tap zones (Instagram-style asset cycling) ───── */

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-bar {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  z-index: 10;
  display: flex;
  gap: 3px;
  padding: 8px 6px 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-seg {
  flex: 1;
  height: 3px;
  border-radius: 1.5px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-seg-fill {
  display: block !important;
  width: 0%;
  height: 100%;
  border-radius: 1.5px;
  background: #fff;
  will-change: width;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-seg-fill[data-done] {
  width: 100%;
  animation: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-seg-fill[data-active] {
  animation: sai-jzqlk4g5-story-fill linear forwards;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-seg-fill[data-paused] {
  animation-play-state: paused;
}

@keyframes sai-jzqlk4g5-story-fill {
  from {
    width: 0%;
  }
  to {
    width: 100%;
  }
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-media {
  position: relative;
  flex: 1;
  width: 100%;
  min-height: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-asset {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-asset[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-asset .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-video {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: contain;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: contain;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-tap {
  display: block !important;
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  z-index: 5;
  cursor: pointer;
  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-tap--prev {
  left: 0;
  width: 30%;
}

.sai-jzqlk4g5__story-tap--next {
  right: 0;
  width: 70%;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .sai-jzqlk4g5__story-tap {
    display: none !important;
  }
}

/* ───── 9. Reduced motion ───── */

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog {
    animation: none;
  }
  .sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slide {
    transition: none;
  }
  .sai-jzqlk4g5__story-seg-fill {
    transition: none !important;
    animation: none !important;
  }
}
{% endstylesheet %}

<script src="{{ 'sai-snippet-jzqlk4g5.js' | asset_url }}" async></script>

{%- assign content = variant.content -%}
{%- assign slot_content = entry.content -%}
{%- assign heading = content.heading -%}
{%- assign subheading = content.subheading -%}
{%- assign card_style = content.card_style | default: 'plain' -%}
{%- assign cta_text = content.cta_text | default: 'Shop now' -%}
{%- assign cta_action = content.cta_action | default: 'redirect' -%}
{%- assign video_handles = slot_content.videoHandles -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    Filter video_handles to videos whose product_tags list contains at
    least one tagged product whose referenced Product resolves on the
    storefront. Storefront Liquid returns nil for draft / archived /
    deleted products, so this naturally hides videos whose tagged
    products are all unpublished. If zero videos remain, the outer
    `if video_handles.size > 0` guard below suppresses the entire
    output — header, grid, dialog, pool — no DOM, no JS bind.
  endcomment
  assign _renderable_handles_csv = ''
  for handle in video_handles
    assign _vid = metaobjects.spectrum_shoppable_video[handle]
    assign _has_renderable_tag = false
    if _vid != blank and _vid.product_tags != blank
      for _t in _vid.product_tags.value
        if _t.product.value != blank
          assign _has_renderable_tag = true
          break
        endif
      endfor
    endif
    if _has_renderable_tag
      if _renderable_handles_csv == ''
        assign _renderable_handles_csv = handle
      else
        assign _renderable_handles_csv = _renderable_handles_csv | append: ',' | append: handle
      endif
    endif
  endfor
  if _renderable_handles_csv == ''
    assign video_handles = '' | split: ','
  else
    assign video_handles = _renderable_handles_csv | split: ','
  endif
-%}

{%- if video_handles.size > 0 -%}
<sai-jzqlk4g5
  class="sai-jzqlk4g5{% unless card_style == 'plain' %} sai-jzqlk4g5--{{ card_style }}{% endunless %}"
  data-cta-text="{{ cta_text | escape }}"
  data-cta-action="{{ cta_action }}"
>
  <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__container">

    {%- comment -%}
      Header + heading + subheading always rendered so applyVariant() can
      flip text and visibility via the `hidden` attribute without DOM
      injection when an experience variant changes either field between
      blank and non-blank at runtime.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__header"{% if heading == blank and subheading == blank %} hidden{% endif %}>
      <h2 class="sai-jzqlk4g5__heading"{% if heading == blank %} hidden{% endif %}>{{ heading }}</h2>
      <p class="sai-jzqlk4g5__subheading"{% if subheading == blank %} hidden{% endif %}>{{ subheading }}</p>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Skeleton placeholders — one per video handle. JS reads data-handle, looks up
      pool[handle], then either replaces the placeholder with a real card
      (pool entry has video_url) or upgrades it to __card--unavailable
      (pool missing or no video_url). Aspect-ratio is reserved by the shared
      __card class so the swap is CLS-free.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__grid" role="list">
      {%- for handle in video_handles -%}
        <div
          class="sai-jzqlk4g5__card sai-jzqlk4g5__card--placeholder"
          data-handle="{{ handle }}"
          aria-hidden="true"
        ></div>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Dialog scaffold only — JS injects slides into __dialog-slides on init
      and on every applyVariant. Nav buttons always emitted with `hidden`;
      JS toggles based on resolved video count after applyVariant runs.
      `__dialog-nav[hidden] { display: none; }` in CSS makes hidden actually
      hide them on tablet+ (where the class rule otherwise wins).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <dialog class="sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="{{ heading | default: 'Video' | escape }}">
      <button class="sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-close" type="button" data-action="close" aria-label="Close video">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
          <path d="M1.5 1.5L12.5 12.5M12.5 1.5L1.5 12.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" />
        </svg>
      </button>

      <button class="sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-mute" type="button" data-action="mute" aria-label="Unmute video">
        <svg class="sai-jzqlk4g5__mute-icon--muted" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M11 5L6 9H2v6h4l5 4V5z" fill="currentColor"/>
          <path d="M23 9l-6 6M17 9l6 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        </svg>
        <svg class="sai-jzqlk4g5__mute-icon--sound" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" style="display:none">
          <path d="M11 5L6 9H2v6h4l5 4V5z" fill="currentColor"/>
          <path d="M15.54 8.46a5 5 0 0 1 0 7.07M19.07 4.93a10 10 0 0 1 0 14.14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>

      <button class="sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav--prev" type="button" data-action="prev" aria-label="Previous video" hidden>
        <svg width="10" height="16" viewBox="0 0 10 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M9 1L1 8L9 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
      <button class="sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-nav--next" type="button" data-action="next" aria-label="Next video" hidden>
        <svg width="10" height="16" viewBox="0 0 10 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M1 1L9 8L1 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>

      <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__dialog-slides"></div>

      {%- comment -%}
        Mini-PDP bottom sheet — single instance per snippet placement, populated
        on demand from the pool block whenever a product card's CTA opens it.
        Sibling of __dialog-slides so the slide swipe / scroll DOM has no effect
        on the sheet's transform. Hidden by default; JS toggles `--open` and
        the `hidden` attribute together so screen-readers don't announce it
        when collapsed.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <aside
        class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop"
        role="dialog"
        aria-modal="true"
        aria-labelledby="sai-jzqlk4g5-qs-title"
        hidden
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-backdrop" data-action="qs-close"></div>
        <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-panel" role="document">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-close"
            data-action="qs-close"
            aria-label="Close"
            title="Close"
          >
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
              <path d="M1.5 1.5L12.5 12.5M12.5 1.5L1.5 12.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" />
            </svg>
          </button>

          <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-header">
            <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-media">
              <img class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-image" data-qs-image alt="" width="600" height="600" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-meta">
              <a class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-title" data-qs-title id="sai-jzqlk4g5-qs-title" href="#"></a>
              <p class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-price">
                <span class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-price-current" data-qs-price></span>
                <span class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-price-compare" data-qs-compare hidden></span>
              </p>
              <a class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-view" data-qs-view data-action="product-click" href="#">
                View product
                <svg class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-view-icon" width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
                  <path d="M4 2L8 6L4 10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-options" data-qs-options></div>

          <button
            type="button"
            class="sai-jzqlk4g5__quickshop-atc"
            data-action="qs-atc"
            disabled
          >Add to cart</button>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </dialog>

  </div>
</sai-jzqlk4g5>

{%- comment -%}
  Bespoke pool — sibling of <sai-jzqlk4g5>, NOT inside it (the JS reads
  it via direct-children iteration on the outer instance container).
  Carries every video's resolved data: video URL (mp4 picked server-side),
  poster URL (image_url filter applied), and the full product_tags array
  with money-formatted prices, variant data, override fields. JS rebuild
  reads this on every variant resolution.

  Pool keying is by metaobject handle (matches entry.content.videoHandles).
  Iteration walks videos_union once — no matching, no filtering;
  a targeted variant whose refIds differ from the default still finds its
  videos here.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script type="application/json" data-spectrum-snippet-pool>
{
  "shoppable_videos":{
    {%- for handle in video_handles -%}
      {%- assign entry = metaobjects.spectrum_shoppable_video[handle] -%}
      {%- if entry -%}
      {%- unless forloop.first -%},{%- endunless -%}

      {%- comment -%}── First-asset URL resolution (for card preview) ──{%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign first_video_url = '' -%}
      {%- assign first_poster_url = '' -%}
      {%- assign first_preview_url = '' -%}
      {%- if entry.assets != blank -%}
        {%- assign total_assets = entry.assets.value.size -%}
        {%- assign first_asset = nil -%}
        {%- for fa in entry.assets.value offset: 0 limit: 1 -%}
          {%- assign first_asset = fa -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
        {%- if first_asset -%}
          {%- assign media_file = first_asset.media.value -%}
          {%- if media_file != blank -%}
            {%- assign asset_type_val = first_asset.asset_type.value | default: 'video' -%}
            {%- if asset_type_val == 'image' -%}
              {%- assign first_poster_url = media_file | image_url: width: 600 -%}
            {%- else -%}
              {%- if media_file.sources != blank -%}
                {%- for source in media_file.sources -%}
                  {%- if source.format == 'mp4' and first_video_url == '' -%}
                    {%- assign first_video_url = source.url -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endfor -%}
                {%- if first_video_url == '' -%}
                  {%- assign first_video_url = media_file.sources.first.url -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- elsif media_file.url != blank -%}
                {%- assign first_video_url = media_file.url -%}
              {%- endif -%}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endif -%}
          {%- if first_asset.poster_image.value != blank -%}
            {%- assign first_poster_url = first_asset.poster_image.value | image_url: width: 600 -%}
          {%- endif -%}
          {%- assign preview_file = first_asset.preview_video.value -%}
          {%- if preview_file != blank -%}
            {%- if preview_file.sources != blank -%}
              {%- for source in preview_file.sources -%}
                {%- if source.format == 'mp4' and first_preview_url == '' -%}
                  {%- assign first_preview_url = source.url -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endfor -%}
              {%- if first_preview_url == '' -%}
                {%- assign first_preview_url = preview_file.sources.first.url -%}
              {%- endif -%}
            {%- elsif preview_file.url != blank -%}
              {%- assign first_preview_url = preview_file.url -%}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      {{ handle | json }}:{
        "title":{{ entry.title | default: 'Video' | json }},
        "assets":[
          {%- if entry.assets != blank -%}
          {%- assign first_asset_json = true -%}
          {%- for i in (0..total_assets) -%}
            {%- if i >= total_assets -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- assign a_ref = nil -%}
            {%- for ref in entry.assets.value offset: i limit: 1 -%}
              {%- assign a_ref = ref -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
            {%- if a_ref -%}
              {%- assign a_type = a_ref.asset_type.value | default: 'video' -%}
              {%- assign a_url = '' -%}
              {%- assign a_poster = '' -%}
              {%- assign a_media = a_ref.media.value -%}
              {%- if a_media != blank -%}
                {%- if a_type == 'image' -%}
                  {%- assign a_url = a_media | image_url: width: 1200 -%}
                {%- else -%}
                  {%- if a_media.sources != blank -%}
                    {%- for source in a_media.sources -%}
                      {%- if source.format == 'mp4' and a_url == '' -%}
                        {%- assign a_url = source.url -%}
                      {%- endif -%}
                    {%- endfor -%}
                    {%- if a_url == '' -%}
                      {%- assign a_url = a_media.sources.first.url -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- elsif a_media.url != blank -%}
                    {%- assign a_url = a_media.url -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if a_ref.poster_image.value != blank -%}
                {%- assign a_poster = a_ref.poster_image.value | image_url: width: 600 -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- unless first_asset_json -%},{%- endunless -%}
              {%- assign first_asset_json = false -%}
              {"type":{{ a_type | json }},"url":{{ a_url | json }},"poster_url":{{ a_poster | json }}}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        ],
        "video_url":{{ first_video_url | json }},
        "poster_url":{{ first_poster_url | json }},
        "preview_url":{{ first_preview_url | json }},
        "product_tags":[
          {%- comment -%}
            Gate on `!= blank` to mirror the original SSR dialog-slides loop.
            Typed-list reference fields are array-typed, so entry.product_tags
            should always be defined on schema-conformant entries; this is
            defensive against unset/nil cases (e.g. an entry written before
            the field existed) where `.value.size` would be nil and `(0..nil)`
            is undefined behaviour in Liquid.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- if entry.product_tags != blank -%}
          {%- assign total_tags = entry.product_tags.value.size -%}
          {%- assign first_tag = true -%}
          {%- for i in (0..total_tags) -%}
            {%- if i >= total_tags -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- assign tagged = nil -%}
            {%- for t in entry.product_tags.value offset: i limit: 1 -%}
              {%- assign tagged = t -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
            {%- if tagged -%}
              {%- assign product = tagged.product.value -%}
              {%- if product -%}
                {%- unless first_tag -%},{%- endunless -%}
                {%- assign first_tag = false -%}
                {%- assign target_variant = tagged.pre_selected_variant.value | default: product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}
                {%- assign single_variant = false -%}
                {%- if product.variants.size == 1 -%}{%- assign single_variant = true -%}{%- endif -%}
                {%- assign display_name = tagged.display_name_override.value | default: product.title -%}
                {%- assign cta_text = tagged.cta_text_override.value | default: 'Add to cart' -%}
                {%- assign thumb_img = tagged.thumbnail_override.value | default: product.featured_image -%}
                {%- assign thumb_url = '' -%}
                {%- if thumb_img != blank -%}
                  {%- assign thumb_url = thumb_img | image_url: width: 160 -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                {%- assign show_compare = false -%}
                {%- if target_variant.compare_at_price > target_variant.price -%}
                  {%- assign show_compare = true -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                {
                  "display_name":{{ display_name | json }},
                  "product_url":{{ product.url | json }},
                  "thumb_url":{{ thumb_url | json }},
                  "price_override":{{ tagged.price_override.value | json }},
                  "cta_text":{{ cta_text | json }},
                  "cta_url":{{ tagged.cta_url_override.value | json }},
                  "single_variant":{{ single_variant | json }},
                  "variant_id":{{ target_variant.id | json }},
                  "variant_available":{{ target_variant.available | json }},
                  "variant_price":{{ target_variant.price | money | json }},
                  "variant_compare_at_price":{{ target_variant.compare_at_price | money | json }},
                  "show_compare":{{ show_compare | json }},
                  "product_price":{{ product.price | money | json }},
                  "cart_url":{{ routes.cart_url | default: '/cart' | json }},
                  "tag_id":{{ tagged.system.id | json }},
                  "product_id":{{ product.id | json }},
                  "handle":{{ product.handle | json }},
                  "available":{{ product.available | json }},
                  "compare_at_price":{%- if show_compare -%}{{ target_variant.compare_at_price | money | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
                  "variants":[
                    {%- assign first_v = true -%}
                    {%- for v in product.variants -%}
                      {%- unless first_v -%},{%- endunless -%}
                      {%- assign first_v = false -%}
                      {%- assign v_img = '' -%}
                      {%- if v.featured_image != blank -%}{%- assign v_img = v.featured_image | image_url: width: 600 -%}{%- endif -%}
                      {
                        "id":{{ v.id | json }},
                        "title":{{ v.title | json }},
                        "available":{{ v.available | json }},
                        "price":{{ v.price | money | json }},
                        "options":[
                          {%- if v.option1 != blank -%}{{ v.option1 | json }}{%- endif -%}
                          {%- if v.option2 != blank -%},{{ v.option2 | json }}{%- endif -%}
                          {%- if v.option3 != blank -%},{{ v.option3 | json }}{%- endif -%}
                        ],
                        "featured_image":{{ v_img | json }}
                      }
                    {%- endfor -%}
                  ],
                  {%- comment -%}
                    Per-product option groupings. Surfaces name + position + values
                    with optional swatch hints (color hex or image URL) when the
                    merchant has configured swatch metaobjects via Shopify's
                    option-value swatch system. Falls back to plain text pills.
                  {%- endcomment -%}
                  "options":[
                    {%- assign first_o = true -%}
                    {%- for opt in product.options_with_values -%}
                      {%- unless first_o -%},{%- endunless -%}
                      {%- assign first_o = false -%}
                      {
                        "name":{{ opt.name | json }},
                        "position":{{ opt.position | json }},
                        "values":[
                          {%- assign first_ov = true -%}
                          {%- for ov in opt.values -%}
                            {%- unless first_ov -%},{%- endunless -%}
                            {%- assign first_ov = false -%}
                            {%- assign sw_color = '' -%}
                            {%- assign sw_image = '' -%}
                            {%- if ov.swatch != blank -%}
                              {%- if ov.swatch.color != blank -%}{%- assign sw_color = ov.swatch.color -%}{%- endif -%}
                              {%- if ov.swatch.image != blank -%}{%- assign sw_image = ov.swatch.image | image_url: width: 80 -%}{%- endif -%}
                            {%- endif -%}
                            {
                              "name":{{ ov.name | json }},
                              "swatch_color":{%- if sw_color != '' -%}{{ sw_color | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
                              "swatch_image":{%- if sw_image != '' -%}{{ sw_image | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%}
                            }
                          {%- endfor -%}
                        ]
                      }
                    {%- endfor -%}
                  ]
                }
              {%- endif -%}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        ]
      }
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  }
}
</script>
{%- endif -%}
